caption: Table 1: Fréchet Inception Distance (FID) on CIFAR-10 and CelebA. Lower is better.
description: This table presents the Fréchet Inception Distance (FID) scores, a metric for evaluating the quality of generated images, for different variational autoencoder (VAE) models trained using the biased and unbiased alpha-divergence minimization algorithms. The results are shown for various values of the alpha parameter (α) and for two datasets: CIFAR-10 and CelebA. Lower FID scores indicate better image generation quality.  The table also includes results for the IWAE (α=0) and standard VAE (α=1) baselines for comparison.

caption: Table 1: Fréchet Inception Distance (FID) on CIFAR-10 and CelebA. Lower is better.
description: This table presents the Fréchet Inception Distance (FID) scores, a metric for evaluating the quality of generated images,  for Variational Autoencoders (VAEs) trained using two different alpha-divergence minimization approaches (VR and UB) on the CIFAR-10 and CelebA image datasets.  Lower FID scores indicate better image generation quality. The results are shown for various values of the alpha parameter (α), which controls the balance between mass-covering and zero-forcing behaviors in the alpha-divergence.
